<body>
  <h1>ToastKit Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> October 26, 2025</p>

  <h2>Overview</h2>
  <p>
    ToastKit by <strong>YvonLabs</strong> is a Chrome extension designed to help you
    reset cookies, cache, and site storage for the site you’re currently on.
    ToastKit is built with privacy as a core principle and does not collect,
    store, or transmit any personal data.
  </p>

  <h2>What Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    ToastKit does not collect, store, or share any information about your browsing
    activity, identity, or device. All actions performed by ToastKit happen
    locally within your browser using Chrome’s built-in APIs.
  </p>

  <h2>How ToastKit Works</h2>
  <p>
    When you click “Toast This Site,” the extension instructs your browser to
    clear cookies, storage, and permissions for the current site. No data is sent
    anywhere, and no information leaves your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    ToastKit does not share data with third parties or external services.
    No analytics, tracking, or logging is implemented.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    Because all processing occurs locally, no external network requests are made
    by ToastKit, minimizing security and privacy risks.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For any questions about this privacy policy, please contact us at:
    <a href="mailto:contact@yvonlabs.eu">contact@yvonlabs.eu</a>
  </p>
</body>
